This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and deep learning, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The comparison between human and machine performance could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the study involves human subjects and their perception, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
